flavor_text_entries.red:
Moves silently
and stealthily.
Eats the eggs of birds, such as
PIDGEY and
SPEAROW, whole.
flavor_text_entries.blue:
Moves silently
and stealthily.
Eats the eggs of birds, such as
PIDGEY and
SPEAROW, whole.
flavor_text_entries.yellow:
The older it gets,
the longer it
grows. At night, it wraps its long
body around tree
branches to rest.
flavor_text_entries.gold:
It can freely de­
tach its jaw to
swallow large prey whole. It can be­
come too heavy to
move, however.
flavor_text_entries.silver:
It always hides in
grass. When first
born, it has no poison, so its
bite is painful,
but harmless.
flavor_text_entries.crystal:
It flutters the
tip of its tongue
to seek out the scent of prey,
then swallows the
prey whole.
flavor_text_entries.ruby:
EKANS curls itself up in a spiral while
it rests.
Assuming this position allows it to quickly respond to a threat from any
direction with a glare from its upraised
head.

flavor_text_entries.emerald:

flavor_text_entries.firered:
A very common sight in grassland, etc.
It flicks its tongue in and out to sense
danger in its surroundings.

flavor_text_entries.ultra-sun:
By dislocating its jaw, it can swallow prey larger
than itself. After a meal, it curls up and rests.
flavor_text_entries.ultra-moon:
The eggs of bird Pokémon are its favorite food.
It swallows eggs whole, so sometimes an egg
gets stuck, and Ekans faints.
